      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Reaction.webp",
      "name": "Warning Peal",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature spends 1 round in area D15.</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The bell rises up and rings twice in quick succession. The first ring alerts all of Scarwall's inhabitants and grants a +5 circumstance bonus to Perception checks of any of Scarwall's inhabitants using the @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Seek]{Seek} action for the next 24 hours. The second ring is even louder and any creature within the stairwell leading up to D15 suffers [[/r {10d10}[sonic]]]{10d10 sonic damage} (@Check[type:fortitude|dc:32|basic:true]) and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Deafened]{Deafened} for 1 hour upon a failed save. All creatures that are within area D15 when the bell rings suffer the same effects as the stairwell but are @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Deafened]{Deafened} for 1 hour upon a successful save and deafened permanently on a failed save.</p>"
        },
